-----------------------------------------------------------------------
On the tenth day, Demeter went to Eleusis in disguise. There King Celeus
and Queen Metaneira entertained her and graciously offered her the
position of wet-nurse to their son Demophoon. IAMBE, the LAME
princess, tried to cheer Demeter up with silly lascivious verses. Baubo,
the dry nurse, joined her in a joke too. (The three of them formed a
Triple-Goddess.) Then, an elder son of Celeus, Abas, accused Demeter of
greediness while she drank Barley-water. Without thinking, Demeter threw
him a grim look, and turned him into a lizard. Later, she felt bad, and
decided to make Demophoon immortal. She put him in her sacred fire,
chanting, to burn away his mortality. Unfortunately, Metaneira came in
before the ceremony was complete, and Demophoon died. Now that was two
sons dead by a goddesses hand, and Celeus began to think his house was
cursed. In his weeping his name got changed to Dysaules (which means
&quot;of an unlucky house&quot;), and Demeter told him to stop weeping, because
she would bestow many gifts upon his third son Triptolemus. Triptolemus
was the one who told her the information she needed about Persephone.

